description: It's alternate-Earth anarchy as Doctor Strange, Captain Marvel, Ghost Rider, Spider-Woman, Nova and Shang-Chi are turned against humanity when fate is tossed a twist by that infamous question mark! Plus: The Howling Commandos fight for Earth, and Spider-Man fights for...ratings!? Featuring the Fantastic Four, Daredevil and Hellstorm! Collects WHAT IF? #14-15 and #17-20.
name: Volume 3

description: After the destruction of his Annie Droid, Kalif has a mental breakdown, spoiling both his sister’s fun and his father’s plans. Feeling responsible, Mary Medea abandons her plans and blasts off to fight the Bajar-backed March Baptist army, ominously leaving a copy of her will behind. Plus: more Galactic Girl Guide action!
name: Change Is In The Heir

description:
"Boys and Their Toys," Part 1 of 2

Somebody has made a movie based on Angel's adventures in hell! Angel and Spike go to a comic con to see how badly Hollywood has mangled true events, only to find themselves surrounded by supernatural evil at every turn. Can Angel tell the difference between an evil demon and a 14-year-old fanboy dressed as an evil demon? Is there a difference?
name: Boys and Their Toys (Part 1)

description: He is the last of thirteen, taught for his entire life that he was born better. A Zemo by blood is a superior person. So then why has he always failed? Now, having been sent hurtling through time, Baron Helmut Zemo will have a chance to encounter the truth of his family as it happened in the past -- when he comes face-to-face with the first of his family line, the legendary Baron Harbin Zemo! But how much of what we know of our family history is truth and how much has been embellished by the perspective of time? Can Zemo find a way to escape his situation, or will he choose to stay trapped in time if it means preventing his family lineage from a legacy of failure? Collecting THUNDERBOLTS PRESENTS: ZEMO - BORN BETTER #1-4.
name: Thunderbolts Presents: Zemo: Born Better
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 1)
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 2)
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 4)
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 5)
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 14)
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 13)
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 11)
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 10)
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 9)
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 8)
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 6)

description: Darth Vader wants Luke Skywalker -- alive. Prince Xizor, the largest trader in the galaxy, wants Skywalker dead. And Skywalker, along with Leia, Chewbacca, and the droids, have a goal of their own: rescue Han Solo. But Solo has been encased in carbonite and taken by the most notorious mercenary in the galaxy, Boba Fett, who intends to deliver him to Jabba the Hutt. It's a clash of good against evil, of right against wrong, and it comes to a head in the Shadows of the Empire . . . Featuring all your favorite characters from the Star Wars motion picture trilogy and a score of new ones, Shadows of the Empire is everything a Star Wars fan could hope for.
name: Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire

volume.name: Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire

description: It's time for the St. White festival, and Daisuke has been so busy working on the festival committee that he's forgotten to get a present for his beloved Risa. His mother, in her infinite generosity, forces Daisuke to take a simple white ribbon as a gift. To top it all off, there's a story going around that if a boy gives a white ribbon to a girl and ties it for her on St. White, they will fall in love ...
name: Vol 3

description: While continuing his relentless pursuit to get the scoop on Dark Mousy, Takeshi becomes distracted by a mysterious young woman in a museum. He falls instantly head over heels for her, and recruits Daisuke to help find out who she is. But the path to love takes them far from home ...
name: Vol 4

description: After barely escaping the fight with Krad, Daisuke find himself with no one to turn to. He has a new enemy out to kill him and Dark is nowhere to be found. When Daisuke receives a clue about Dark's whereabouts, he goes on a search-and-rescue mission for the phantom thief. Meanwhile, Riku and Risa manage to get each other lost, sending their classmates into a manic panic!
name: Vol 5

description: Things go from bad to worse when Daisuke is taken away by Time's Second-Hand, which Dark failed to steal. The only remaining link to Daisuke lies within the painting, which he had unwittingly given to Riku the day before. Dark now has to retrieve the painting--while pretending to be Daisuke!
name: Vol 7

description: The Artist and the Thief Dark has retrieved the painting from Riku...but the sisters decide to get it back. What they don't know is that Daisuke is actually trapped in the painting and Dark has to set him free before time runs out! Humanity is questioned and love put to the test in this exciting volume of DNAngel!
name: Vol 8

description: The production of the class play finally hits the stage, and even though Daisuke was a little embarrassed to play a girl, he soon realizes that giving a good performance in the part of Freedert is the least he can do for his magical friend. Later, there's a series of transformations and troubled sleep, when a near kiss from Daisuke to Riku changes him into Dark. Then, when Dark plants one on Risa, he changes back into Daisuke--something that has never happened before!
name: Vol 9

description: When Risa and Dark--who's actually Wiz in disguise--go to a popular new horror movie, Wiz is nearly scared to death! Meanwhile, Riku and Daisuke are enjoying their time alone, although Daisuke's trying not to have too good of a time, lest he change into Dark and blow the whole thing. Later, Risa expresses her unconditional love for Dark, who hints that he may not be everything he seems.
name: Vol 10

description: Paul Jenkins’ (MYTHOS) run on Theater of War comes to a close, in this, his most personal and poignant tale of the legacy of Captain America. From America’s first Independence Day, through wars that nearly tore the country apart, to the rebirth of a nation, the spirit of Captain America has always been with us. And no one embodies that better than Steve Rogers.
name: Ghosts of My Country

volume.name: Captain America Theater of War: Ghosts of My Country

description:
Story Lists:

  1. The Present (Green Lantern Kyle Rayner/Green Arrow Connor Hawke) - Written by Devin Grayson; Art Will Rosado and Sal Buscema
  2. The House of Peace (Batman) - Written by Chuck Dixon; Art Dave Taylor and Wayne Faucher
  3. Present Tense (Darkseid) - Written, illustrated, colored and lettered all by Ty Templeton
  4.  Twas the Night Before Kwanzaa (Black Lighting) - Written by Tony Isabella; Art Eddie Newell
  5. The Gift (Superman) - Written and penciled by Dan Jurgens; inks Brett Breeding
  6. I left my heart at the Justice Society Canteen (JSA) - Written by Howard Chaykin; Art Rick Burchett
  7. A Christmas Carol (Sgt. Rock) - Written by Chuck Dixon; Art Russ Heath
  8. The Old Lane (Nightwing and Oracle) Co-plotter/Penciler Brian Stelfreeze; Co-plotter/dialogue Devin Grayson; inks Karl Story.
  9. Ornaments Page - Art by Rick Burchett

Story List:

  1. The Benefaction of Peace (Superman) - Written by Barry Jameson; Art by Graham Nolan and Josef Rubinstien
  2. A high Father Christmas (Orion & Highfather of the New Gods) - Written by Walter Simonson; Art by Sal Buscema
  3. Bearing Gifts We Traverse Afar (Catwoman) - Written by Dennis O'Neil; Art by Jesse Delperdang and Mike Sellers
  4. Satan's Little Helper (The Demon) - Written, lettered and fully illustrated by Ty Templeton
  5. The Vessel (Green Lantern Kyle Rayner) - Written by Michael Jan Friedman; Art Roger Robinson and Phyllis Novin
  6. Present Tense (The Flash/Wally West) - Written by Brian Augustyn and Mark Waid; Art by Paul Ryan and Dick Giordano
  7. Just Another Night (Batman Family) - Written and pencils by Jim Aparo, inks and colors by Kevin Nowlan

Bunnie is back, but worse for wear with her wounds being tended in the hospital. Luckily, her friends are by her side, but not for long as Eggman attacks in his Egg-Tortoise walker! Sonic and Tails spring into action, while Iron Queen and crew watch with wide eyes. Why are they so interested in seeing Eggman captured?

In a stroke of luck, Eggman escapes his padded cell, aiming to destroy his hated enemy. He finds Sonic, who has nothing but pity for him.

Robotnik's escape has created complications with the Iron Queen's plans, who wants the problem removed immediately.
name: On the Run - Pt 1

description:
Join Superman, Supergirl, Batwoman, Shazam, Green Lantern, The Flash and Shadowpact as they spread the joy of the new season in their own special ways. This giant-sized 80-page Special features stories by Greg Rucka, Judd Winick, Bill Willingham, Joe Kelly, Kelley Puckett, Keith Champagne, and Ian Boothby.

Contents

  • Green Lantern in "A Hector Hammond Christmas", written by Keith Champagne, art by John Byrne and Champagne
  • Shadowpact in "Christmas Spirits", written by Bill Willingham, art by Cory Walker
  • Supergirl in "All I want for Christmas...", written by Joe Kelly, art by Ale Garza
  • Trials of Shazam in "Gift of the Magi", written by Tony Bedard, Art by Marcos Marz and Luciana Del Negro
  • The Flash in "Father Christmas", written by Ian Boothby, Art by Giuseppe Camuncoli and Lorenzo Ruggiero
  • Batwoman in "Lights", written by Greg Rucka, art by Christian Alamy
  • Superman in "Yes, Tyrone, There is a Santa Claus" *Elsewords*, written by Kelley Puckett. Art by Pete Woods.

The Elephant with the Gold Tusks, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is shoved off of an elephant by Langwell and she lands on the ground so hard she is knocked unconscious. The masked Langwell points his gun at her to finish her off...

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka is apparently shot in the back by Langwell and she falls helplessly into the river.

The Marauding Maniacs of the Jungle, Ch. 1 cliffhanger ending - Nyoka and her companions are surrounded by natives with spears and they are about to throw them!

Ch. 2 cliffhanger ending - A rock is thrown at Nyoka's head and it knocks her unconscious. A black jaguar is in a tree above the girl. The jaguar is looking down at her, ready to pounce.
name: The Elephant with the Gold Tusks, The Marauding Maniacs of the Jungle

description: An alternate universe where Daredevil and Batman coexist. Though they do not like each other they are forced to work together to stop the combined might of Two-face and Mr. Hyde.
name: Eye For An Eye

description: When his school bus crashes, teenage karate star Rando is sent into a coma. A year later he wakes up to find that his disfigured face has been reconstructed in the image of the girl he has a crush on! Not knowing what Rando originally looked like, the mad plastic surgeon Dr. Manabe used a photo in Rando's pocket as the model for his reconstructive surgery. Abandoned by his friends and parents, the all-new Rando is mistaken for his would-be girlfriend's long-lost twin sister and adopted into her family. Can he put aside his feelings and be a good "big sister" to Rina...when he's still a teenage boy from the waist down?
name: Vol. 1

description: The Year One Annuals continue, exploring pivotal events and untold stories of the DC Universe's greatest heroes…and in this case, villains! The year's most unusual Year One Annual looks at the previous lives of Superman's monstrous killer. Cursed with the ability to return after every mortal defeat, Doomsday has survived countless "Year Ones." Four tales are told of the Armageddon Creature's rampage through the cosmos, before his fateful first encounter with the Man of Steel.
name: Communion

description: Rando struggles to be a good "big sister" to Rina as fate conspires to put him in one disastrous situation after another. When pants start coming off, and half-naked women start crawling all over him for the thinnest of reasons, Rando must use all his karate wiles to avoid being exposed as a complete weirdo. Meanwhile, will the mad Dr. Manabe succeed in his plan to remove the last remnants of Rando's manhood...or will Rando remove Dr. Manabe's brains with his fist? It's 7.5 inches of manga heaven!
name: Vol. 2

description: Rando is tempted by some girl-on-fake-girl action when he meets Nozomi, a girl who just loves beautiful women who kick men's butts. Too bad Rando has a man's butt that he has to hide when he's forced to spend the day at the pool! Can he get help from Dr. Manabe, whose solution to every problem is to try to convince Rando to trade up to a "G-cup" set of fake breasts? Then, the need for extra cash leads Rando to accept a dubious job offer involving a full-coverage bodysuit...and does Rando have a male admirer too?
name: Vol. 3
The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 3)

description:
This Halloween, you're in fo a really spooky threat from the Star Wars universe! Han Solo and his best pal, Chewbacca, stumble upon something frightenin when they become stranded on a planet shrouded in a deep and mysterious fog... It's a classic Star Wars adventure featuring your favorite Star Wars heroes - with a little Halloween twist!  
 
This 16 page mini comic came packaged with Previews and reprints a story from Star Wars Tales # 17.

name: The Travails Of Ms. Nagi Mahori (part 7)

description: The first property from Top Cow and Heroes & Villains Entertainment is here! Enter a world of werewolves and serial killers unlike anything you've seen before. This limited First Look was previously available only at San Diego Comic-Con.

Having learned about the terminal condition of Captain Steel, Judo Girl takes the good fight to the archest of her arch-foes, seeking to stop his suicide plot, one that will destroy the entire world! Along the way, she must overcome ninjas, underlings, and her own brother, Judo-Bot.
name: The Gental Way-Part Four

description: Judo Girl races to save her brother, Judo Boy, from Captain Steel's lab, but first she'll have to fight her way through violent obstacles and legions of minions. But things only go from bad to worse as Judo Girl later faces off against the Judo-BOT! Can Judo Girl defeat Judo-Bot and save her brother? And if so, how will Judo Girl survive to the surprise that Captain Steel has waiting for her?
name: The Gental Way-Part Three

description: Judo Girl is saved from Judo-Bot by her new friend Saul... who learns that heroism comes with a heavy price. Judo-Bot makes good his escape, taking his eclectic booty: the Biofractal Scanner... and a dead body! Also, on the fab flip-side, set during the groovy Silver Age, a radioactive meteorite transforms Judo Boy into a brutish, 50-foot-tall giant! Judo Girl worries that her big, BIG brother will attack her... but all's square when the newly-named Judo Giant tries to help, then the real problems begin!
name: The Gental Way-Part Two

description: The X-Men are back from space! Well, half of them, anyway. The team is shattered, broken and separated. The group that has returned to Earth is finding it much worse than how they left it - especially underground. Attacks in the Morlock Tunnels immediately grab the X-Men's attention. What do these attacks have to do with the future of the mutant race? Maybe special guest-star Storm can get to the bottom of all this! Collecting UNCANNY X-MEN #487-491.
name: Uncanny X-Men: Extremists

description:
For millions of years, mankind's place on Earth was unchallenged - until five young people paved the way for a new kind of human. While students at the Xavier School for Gifted Youngsters, Cyclops, Marvel Girl, Angel, Beast and Iceman taught the world what it meant to be X-Men. These are the hidden stories of the team that laid the foundation of a mutant dynasty!

Collects X-Men: First Class (2006) #1-8.
name: Volume 1

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Reprints X-Men: First Class #11-16 and Giant-Sized X-Men: First Class.
name: X-Men: First Class: The Wonder Years

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

volume.name: X-Men: First Class: The Wonder Years

description: A return to the acclaimed universe created by Neil Gaiman and Andy Kubert picks as THE SPIDER has reached manhood in the New World! The young nation has grown peacefully, but Norman Osbourne's treachery finds a way to spoil the peace and put Peter's life on a new course — back to Europe. Jeff Parker [AGENTS OF ATLAS] joins artist Ramon Rosanas to begin the final story of the 1602 saga!
name: The Web Complete: Chapter 1

description: When he discovers a clue to the location of Rina's real twin sister, Rando goes on a road trip in search of the girl whose identity he's stolen. But a guy in a short skirt can get in a lot of trouble traveling alone...and even more trouble when Rina comes along for the ride! Then, our hero stays at a hot spring with suspiciously skeevy proprietors, and a karate-kicking tomboy wants to get her hands on Rando's secret! Pretty Face: the manga where panty shots are the last thing you want!
name: Vol. 4

description: "Yuna is really a guy!" Natsuo has discovered Rando's secret, with no convenient amnesia plot devices in sight! Can Rando pretend to be a girl after his fake breasts fall off in front of the entire class? More importantly, can he ease Natsuo's feelings of betrayal…or is the ultimate taboo actually the ultimate turn- on? Then, the entire cast goes cosplaying, Rando's knitting skills prove to be lacking, and Rando is forced to go on a date with Dr. Manabe!
name: Vol. 5

description: The war is on for Rando's affections when Natsuo and Nozomi finally meet! Which of the class's toughest girls will have their way with our not-quite-male, not-quite-shemale hero? Then, Rando finally meets the person whose face he's been wearing all this time: Rina's real twin sister! Will the return of Yuna spell the end of Rando's womanhood...and when the bandages come off, will his chances with Rina be over?
name: Vol. 6
Beware, The Comics of the Damned!

description: Billy Moon is a martial arts enthusiast and Vietnam veteran who has found a career in roller derby. In the wake of the murder of his best friend by biker gangs, Moon sinks into depression, only to meet a young "beaner" boy named Paco. Paco's comic-book collection inspires Moon to wrap a scarf around his face and fight crime with his roller skates. Drugs dealing bikers are thwarted in their efforts by Skateman, a masked hero on roller skates.

The Challs are back! But with Multi-Man holding June Robbins hostage, can even they snatch victory from the jaws of defeat?

Note: Four years after being cancelled, DC relaunched Challengers of the Unknown with this issue.
name: Multi-Man's Master Plan

description:
Doctor Monroe holds June, bound and captive, and threatens to throw her to M'Nagala if the Challengers don't do as he says.

Following a brief, one sided fight, the Challengers are forced to concede to his demands, namely traveling to London to perform an arcane ritual.

Meanwhile Clayburne thinks Dr. Alec Holland can be of assistance, so he travels to Oregon to retrieve him.
name: The Seven Doorways to Destiny!

description:
Deadman is sent to help heal the still ailing Prof Haley. When he revives, he insists that the Challengers try to help cure the Swamp Thing for all his help.

The Challengers return to Perdition, PA, but find no trace of the Swamp Thing. Deadman, taking possession of Ace reveals to the Challengers that the Swamp Thing is in fact in Philadelphia now - and he's in trouble!
name: To Save A Monster

description:
Red Ryan in a jealous rage picks a fight with Rocky. Deadman, Swamp Thing and June break it up, but Ryan quits the team.

Meanwhile a giant box appears in Toronto. The Canadian authorities are incapable of dealing with it, so they call the Challengers for help.

In trying to enter the box, Deadman accidentally sets free a giant monster, and it's up to the Challengers to save the city!
name: The Creature from the End of Time

description:
Monsters from the future are appearing in Challenger Mountain, and Prof Haley is doing his best to fight them off single-handedly, despite recovering from injury.

Similarly, in Metropolis, Red Ryan, who quit the team, is himself fighting a future-monster on his own.

The rest of the Challengers have traveled to the distant future, where they are attacked and imprisoned by Rip Hunter and and the Sunset Lords he serves.

With Deadman the only one free to act, can the Sunset Lords be stopped?
name: The War at Time's End

description:
12 million years in the future, three of the Challengers break free of captivity, and along with Deadman and Swamp Thing, lead a revolution to free society from the oppression of the Sunset Lords.

While in the present, the remaining two Challengers fight an invasion of monsters from the future.
name: Twelve Million Years to Twilight
None Shall Escape the Walking Evil

description: Features the first chapter of Planetary Book 1: All Over the World and Other Stories graphic novel.
name: Issue 1

volume.name: Just Imagine Stan Lee With Gary Frank Creating Shazam!
Just Imagine Stan Lee With Scott McDaniel Creating Aquaman
Just Imagine Stan Lee With Jerry Ordway Creating JLA
Just Imagine Stan Lee With John Cassaday Creating Crisis
Just Imagine Stan Lee . . . Secret Files and Origins

description: The road to CRISIS begins here as Stan Lee teams up with John Byrne & Terry Austin to present his take on Robin! An orphan gifted with great agility and intellect, the boy who would one day become Robin fell prey to the mysterious machinations of Reverend Dominic Darrk, who now orders him to attack Batman. Will the reluctant Robin find the strength to defy Darrk's commands? Plus, a backup "On the Street" story by Michael Uslan (with Lee), illustrated by the legendary John Severin (DESPERADOES: QUIET OF THE GRAVE).

volume.name: Just Imagine Stan Lee With John Byrne Creating Robin

description:
Kohanamaru comes from a peculiar family--each member can switch bodies with his or her soul mate! His parents can switch bodies, and his aunt, oddly enough, can switch with her cat! Now it's Kohanamaru's turn... When Kohanamaru literally runs into Nanao, the girl of his dreams, they switch bodies. True love, right? Well, unfortunately, she's in love with someone else. And if that weren't bad enough, the "someone else" turns out to be Kohanamaru's twin brother Konatsu...who can reverse their transformation with his own kiss!

Contents

  • FIRST KISSxxx
  • SECOND KISSxxx
  • THIRD KISSxxx
  • FOURTH KISSxxx
  • FIFTH KISSxxx
name: Vol. 1

description:
Who would suspect that Hanamaru and Nanao could switch bodies? Who else but Madoka, the school's paranormal geek? This crazy stalker will do anything to uncover a newsworthy secret! As Hanamaru fends her off, Nanao trains for the big archery tournament...but what will happen when she and Hanamaru switch bodies on the day of the competition?!

Contents

  • SIXTH KISSxxx
  • SEVENTH KISSxxx
  • EIGHTH KISSxxx
  • NINTH KISSxxx
  • TENTH KISSxxx
  • THROW A KISSxxx
name: Vol. 2
